\begin_layout Standard
If tap water is used,
 reaction between the carbon in the water and the acid might build pressure.
 In the first time I put a sealed bottle on the shaker,
 it (probably) exploded and broke one of the holder arms.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Otherwise the acid should be completely safe,
 having a citric acid concentration less than one hundredth that of natural lemon,
 and no other ingredients.
\end_layout

