\begin_layout Standard
The way I straightened the wires goes like this:
 take the wire roll,
 pull out the required length of tantalum with a fine spare.
 Fix the tail (either with a bench vise,
 a pliers pair or by another way),
 hold the head with a pliers pair and pull abruptly.
 Tantalum is (maybe exceptionally) malleable,
 so it will straighten smoothly.
 Note that the head might be torn,
 but usually what's left is long enough to use.
\end_layout

